cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.SY

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses a technique for improving the training of a reinforcement learning agent. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves training an agent to play a video game. Additionally, since the inputs are based on internal game memory values, it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.GR (Graphics) as these fields often deal with image or video data. Finally, since the agent is learning to control a game, it could also be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
